00:01:03.601 --> 00:01:06.033 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughter)

00:01:07.467 --> 00:01:08.300 position:27% line:89% align:start
Thank you, Elly.

00:01:09.834 --> 00:01:11.000 position:19% line:89% align:start
You're so protective.

00:01:13.167 --> 00:01:14.467 position:24% line:89% align:start
You got mad for me.

00:01:15.501 --> 00:01:17.000 position:24% line:89% align:start
Thank you for that.

00:01:20.634 --> 00:01:22.901 position:13% line:5% align:start
Illegally rearing dragons?

00:01:22.934 --> 00:01:25.100 position:16% line:5% align:start
Yep. Or that's the word
on the street.

00:01:25.133 --> 00:01:27.300 position:13% line:5% align:start
We got a hot tip that
someone's doing just that

00:01:27.334 --> 00:01:29.467 position:21% line:83% align:start
in Reverse London's
west district.

00:01:29.501 --> 00:01:31.868 position:21% line:83% align:start
This'll be huge if
it's actually true.

00:01:31.901 --> 00:01:34.334 position:16% line:83% align:start
But why do we get stuck
taking care of it?

00:01:35.667 --> 00:01:38.000 position:27% line:89% align:start
Well, I mean...

00:01:38.033 --> 00:01:40.934 position:19% line:83% align:start
Our job is to rear and
take care of dragons.

00:01:40.968 --> 00:01:42.634 position:5% line:89% align:start
I guess illegally reared dragons

00:01:42.667 --> 00:01:44.267 position:10% line:89% align:start
count under that definition.

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:45.234 position:35% line:89% align:start
Seriously?

00:01:45.267 --> 00:01:46.901 position:16% line:89% align:start
That's a bit of a reach.

00:01:46.934 --> 00:01:48.100 position:19% line:89% align:start
Count yourself lucky.

00:01:48.133 --> 00:01:50.167 position:16% line:83% align:start
That "reach" is putting
money in your pocket.

00:01:54.934 --> 00:01:56.734 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh, very mature.

00:01:56.767 --> 00:01:58.267 position:16% line:89% align:start
You did that on purpose.

00:01:58.300 --> 00:01:59.067 position:35% line:89% align:start
Whoopsie.

00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:01.167 position:24% line:89% align:start
Wow, did I do that?

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:03.801 position:5% line:83% align:start
Hey. It looks like all that cool
stuff you did yesterday

00:02:03.834 --> 00:02:06.234 position:21% line:83% align:start
didn't make it
into the newspaper.

00:02:06.267 --> 00:02:07.968 position:19% line:83% align:start
Even though you
saved the entire city

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:09.133 position:24% line:89% align:start
from a dark dragon.

00:02:10.467 --> 00:02:11.901 position:19% line:83% align:start
Well, that's only
because you're reading

00:02:11.934 --> 00:02:13.767 position:27% line:83% align:start
the Front London
articles, Balgo.

00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:16.300 position:5% line:89% align:start
Here's the Reverse London news.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:20.968 position:35% line:89% align:start
Amazing!

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:22.267 position:19% line:89% align:start
Look, it's you, Noel!

00:02:23.133 --> 00:02:25.467 position:10% line:89% align:start
Man, you look so super cool!

00:02:25.501 --> 00:02:27.567 position:13% line:83% align:start
Uh, hello?
I worked my butt off too.

00:02:27.601 --> 00:02:28.567 position:21% line:89% align:start
Thank you very much.

00:02:28.601 --> 00:02:29.634 position:30% line:89% align:start
Ah, found it!

00:02:29.667 --> 00:02:31.901 position:5% line:89% align:start
This is what I was looking for.

00:02:31.934 --> 00:02:33.934 position:19% line:89% align:start
Whoa, that was close.

00:02:33.968 --> 00:02:37.000 position:13% line:83% align:start
Forgot to share something
important with ya.

00:02:37.033 --> 00:02:40.267 position:13% line:83% align:start
The order came with a
small additional request.

00:02:40.300 --> 00:02:42.267 position:38% line:89% align:start
(awing)

00:02:44.701 --> 00:02:46.200 position:10% line:89% align:start
Why in the world do we have

00:02:46.234 --> 00:02:47.901 position:24% line:83% align:start
to bring him along
with us anyway?

00:02:47.934 --> 00:02:49.133 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's like the chief said.

00:02:49.167 --> 00:02:50.934 position:21% line:83% align:start
Since Balgo draws
dragons toward him,

00:02:50.968 --> 00:02:52.901 position:19% line:83% align:start
he's the perfect lure
to bring them to us

00:02:52.934 --> 00:02:54.734 position:21% line:83% align:start
and help us round
them up efficiently.

00:02:54.767 --> 00:02:56.801 position:7% line:89% align:start
So we need him on the mission.

00:02:56.834 --> 00:02:58.067 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yeah I got that much!

00:02:58.100 --> 00:03:00.000 position:7% line:89% align:start
I was in the room too, y'know.

00:03:00.667 --> 00:03:02.133 position:16% line:89% align:start
Then why are you so mad?

00:03:02.167 --> 00:03:04.601 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm not mad because I didn't
understand the concept!

00:03:04.634 --> 00:03:07.100 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm mad because I have doubts
about this whole thing!

00:03:07.133 --> 00:03:08.434 position:10% line:89% align:start
If you drew the short straw

00:03:08.467 --> 00:03:10.067 position:19% line:83% align:start
and had to look
after the class frog,

00:03:10.100 --> 00:03:11.601 position:5% line:89% align:start
you'd be pissed about it, right?

00:03:11.634 --> 00:03:13.133 position:16% line:89% align:start
Like you'd still do it,

00:03:13.167 --> 00:03:16.300 position:5% line:83% align:start
but you wouldn't be happy
about it, you know what I mean?

00:03:16.334 --> 00:03:18.467 position:16% line:83% align:start
Balgo, she seems to have
taken issue with you.

00:03:18.501 --> 00:03:20.467 position:21% line:83% align:start
Do you have anything
to say about that?

00:03:20.767 --> 00:03:22.133 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yup!

00:03:22.167 --> 00:03:24.734 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm so glad whatever weird
dragon-summon-y thing

00:03:24.767 --> 00:03:27.901 position:10% line:83% align:start
that's going on with my body
will help you out, Noel!

00:03:27.934 --> 00:03:30.467 position:24% line:83% align:start
And if my arms
start to slide up,

00:03:30.501 --> 00:03:32.434 position:21% line:83% align:start
they might brush
against your boobs.

00:03:32.467 --> 00:03:34.934 position:24% line:83% align:start
Just the thought
of getting to bask

00:03:34.968 --> 00:03:37.400 position:13% line:83% align:start
in the warm aura emanating
from your body...

00:03:37.434 --> 00:03:39.067 position:30% line:89% align:start
(giggle/sigh)

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:40.467 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'm a very blessed man.

00:03:40.501 --> 00:03:42.000 position:24% line:89% align:start
I could die happy.

00:03:42.033 --> 00:03:44.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
You do realize that if
I drop you right now,

00:03:44.467 --> 00:03:45.267 position:21% line:89% align:start
you'll probably die.

00:03:45.300 --> 00:03:46.467 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right?

00:03:46.501 --> 00:03:47.300 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Balgo] Huh?

00:03:53.367 --> 00:03:54.267 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Noel] Oh, yeah.

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:56.000 position:21% line:83% align:start
I have something
to give you, Balgo.

00:03:56.934 --> 00:03:58.400 position:33% line:89% align:start
Here you go.

00:03:58.434 --> 00:04:00.901 position:24% line:83% align:start
This is a Piper's
mantle and pipe.

00:04:00.934 --> 00:04:02.367 position:7% line:89% align:start
You'll be working with us now.

00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:04.601 position:13% line:83% align:start
So the chief thought it
would be for the best if,

00:04:04.634 --> 00:04:07.300 position:10% line:83% align:start
